The paper focuses on deep learning solutions for learning control policies in robotics applications, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper discusses both deep reinforcement learning and imitation learning, which are subfields of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of computer vision techniques for robotics applications, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the challenge of transferring policies trained in simulation to real-world scenarios, which is a problem in control systems (cs.SY).
